    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I have similar demand for conditional statement inside definition, which is claimed here #573 . Since it's not trivial to implement that, I propose another way to workaround:\r\n\r\n```\r\nctypedef struct ohmygod:\r\n      int common\r\n\r\nIF UNAME_SYSNAME == \"Windows\":\r\n      ctypedef struct ohmygod:\r\n            int greece\r\nELSE:\r\n      ctypedef struct ohmygod:\r\n            float pelvis\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat is to allow partial definition in Cython (this feature is like [\"partial\" keyword in C#](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/programming-guide/classes-and-structs/partial-classes-and-methods)). I have tried this idea, Cython won't report error but simply ignore the second definition. Is this way easier to implement in Cython?",
    "closed_at": "2019-08-13T16:57:08Z",
