            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Cython won't report error but simply ignore the second definition\r\n\r\nInteresting. It should definitely report an error for this. And I would not want this as a feature, because it makes it hard to understand for users what the actual definition of the struct is. It should be defined in one place, not split across multiple definitions, each of which is incomplete (and wrong) by itself.",
